profile_positions.description:
Shell HR Transformation:
•	Strategic Organization Design of a combined HR and IT funnel model for all HR and IT demand of change requests - joint effort with Shell HR CI Master. Design adopted, embedded and effective;
•	Organization Design to manage impact of configuration requests and releases in HRIT landscape, including SaaS solutions (Workday, SalesForce) and legacy systems with Managed Services support, for coordinated aligned testing and deployments. Design adopted, further detailed by project, embedded and highly effective;
•	Creating the job descriptions for the IT roles in the Workday scaled DevOps model, including Chief Scrum Master, Scrum Masters, etc. Recruiting the teams who delivered Release 1 of the Workday implementation.
•	Chief Scrum Master for Salesforce HR ORG
•	Strategic Design for the interim scaled DevOps model for Salesforce HR ORG, scaling up Agile ways of working between Salesforce CRM, Performance Assessment Tool, Employee Community, Ace;
•	Strategic Design to manage impact of change requests of each Salesforce app in the Salesforce ORG for coordinated aligned testing and deployments in the landscape. Design embedded and operational risks removed. Design used as example for the 2nd iteration of the Workday support model;
•	Continual alignment in the Salesforce HR ORG with the Chief Product Owner, Product Owners, Scrum Masters, Architects and other stakeholders. Achieved quick scale up enabling timely and secure PAT and Employee Community go life;
•	IT Operations Management for Salesforce HR, Payroll EUAF, Talent, Recruitment. Including onboarding and management of suppliers, market standards, managed services;
•	IT Operations SME and FP for RFP for new global SaaS solutions in the HR Transformation program
•	CI Practitioner Project for CIP certification: improving stakeholder engagement to double the CI initiatives in DS T&S IT. L2 benefit. Fits in new IT CI strategy. Solution expected to be replicated to the rest of Shell IT.

•	Strategic Design of the scaled DevOps HRIT model for the global Workday landscape in Shell, including detailed organization design with groupings in a Scrum of Scrums structure and efficient ways of working within the teams and linking teams in Shell HR and IT. Model was adopted, embedded then detailed further and live since April 2019;
•	Identify and manage a complex matrix of senior stakeholders (EVP and VP level -VP-2)) across the HR and IT Functions for acceptance of the strategic design to embed;
•	Develop and execute a transition plan – recognizing the phased Workday SaaS deployment plan and continued need to support legacy applications throughout the transition and thereafter;
•	Design IT roles and ways of working between HR and IT teams in the Scrum of Scrums and the linking HR IT support and delivery teams and HR business teams for the go live of Workday in Shell in April 2019. All roles posted, hired and trained;
•	Provide input to the design of the HR roles and ways of working between HR and IT teams – including Product Owner roles

•	Strategic Design of the Salesforce Case Management DevOps operating model with detailed organization structures, skills, resources, roles, responsibilities for Product Owners, Process Architect, Scrum Master, DevOps teams, HR Operations teams, and linking teams. Embedded, effectively ran since go live and served as example for the Workday scaled DevOps model;
•	Strategic Design of a demand management framework for changes for Salesforce DevOps including roles and responsibilities on strategic and tactical level in HR and IT. Embedded, effectively ran since go live and served as example for the Workday scaled DevOps model
•	Design of DevOps model for Kenexa Open Resourcing, Scrum Master of DevOps team, mature ways of working, achieving delivering value to the business 3 times quicker after 8 months;
•	Manage support suppliers and turn around the end user experience for the Support Service for Learning, including Shell Open University, which services over 175,000 internal and external users;
•	DevOps SME to the Shell Functional Excellence team designing the standard Shell Enterprise Change Management process for DevOps through Kaizen events.

•	Improve enhancement management process between BI, DV and SOM. Reduced enhancement delivery time and operational risks significantly;
•	Transition 15 projects into operations ensuring secure, reliable and affordable operations;
•	Outsource Tier 2 and Tier 3 support to WIPRO for HR IT Learning.
•	Managing operations of the Global Functions HR Non SAP landcape. Delivering secure, reliable and affordable IT services and operations across Shell, including online learning applications like Shell Open University, Moodle, LCMS. Managing a team of 4 Operate Landscape Managers who manage the day to day delivery of secure and reliable operations with suppliers through KPI reports, contract management, license management.

Contacted by GPR.
Keeping an up to date CMDB for Ministry VROM and PCM; 
Ensured all ITIL processes leading to an updated CMDB were improved by leading a data mismatch exercise. Defined and filled gaps in some ITIL processes leading to an improved up to date CMDB
